main event: A lighted object was sighted over the Icelandic Sea at 2300z on June 5, 1962.
interesting points: The object appeared 15 degrees above the horizon for about 15 minutes., The object's course was 200 degrees at 35 miles per hour., Contact was lost at 2315z., The apparent size of the object was about 1/50 of the full moon., No further information available regarding the incident.
witness description: No further details on witnesses available.
